  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>ChinaFAQs climate and energy experts and top media representatives took part in a ChinaFAQs press call on July 8th to preview the July 10th and 11th U.S.-China Strategic and Economic Dialogue (S&amp;ED), which for the first time will include a designated <a href="http://www.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2013/04/207465.htm">Climate Change Working Group</a>.  ChinaFAQs network experts discussed recent events and potential areas of U.S.-China cooperation, including air pollution, shale gas, carbon capture and storage (CCS) and more. The experts also offered insights into what the S&amp;ED will mean for U.S.</p></div>
