  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/chinas-latest-energy-consumption-data-reveals-new-opportunities-and-challenges-0">China‚Äôs latest energy consumption data reveals new opportunities and challenges</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/construction&#32;worker.jpg" alt="" title="" width="180" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>The Chinese Government recently announced the long-awaited provincial energy consumption data for 2011.  The data shows that China‚Äôs energy intensity in 2011 was 0.793 tons coal equivalent (tce) per unit gross domestic product (GDP), 2.01% less than 2010.  The data also reveals new opportunities and challenges for achieving China‚Äôs energy intensity target under the Twelfth Five-Year Plan (12FYP) (2011-2015).</p></div>
