  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/experts-weigh-future-coal-use-china">Experts Weigh In on the Future of Coal Use in China</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/tianjin_10-6-10.jpg" alt="" title="" width="200" height="117" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>Coal will remain a critical part of China‚Äôs energy mix for decades to come, but growth will slow and then peak at perhaps 3.4 billion tons per year by 2020, Jiang Kejun of China‚Äôs Energy Research Institute told a group assembled for the WRI-US CAN-organized briefing on China and coal during the Tianjin climate negotiations on Monday.</p></div>
  </div>
