  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../library/chinafaqs-getting-smarter-about-electricity">ChinaFAQs: Getting Smarter About Electricity</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/ChinaFAQs_Getting_Smarter_About_Electricity-1.png" alt="" title="" width="93" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"><div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../files/chinainfo/ChinaFAQs_Getting_Smarter_About_Electricity_0.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=258315">ChinaFAQs_Getting_Smarter_About_Electricity.pdf</a></div></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><b>Key Points</b></p>

<ul>
<li>China has embarked on a major effort to develop more reliable and ‚Äúsmarter‚Äù electric power grids by 2020.</li>
<li>A smarter grid will help China curb greenhouse gas emissions by reducing electricity losses during transmission, connecting more renewable power sources (such as wind), and improving end-user efficiency.</li>
<li>An emerging technology globally, smart grid technologies are an important area for U.S.-China cooperation.</li>
</ul></div>
  </div>
